Areas where Tree growth hindered by low temperatures & short growing seasons
From Kilden Sami word tundar - "uplands", "treeless mountain tract"
Vegetation composed of dwarf shrubs, sedges & grassess, mosses, & lichens
Some trees may grow
The ecotone (or ecological boundary region) between the tundra and the forest is known as the tree line or timberline.


